  "texts": [
    "They are often regarded as the ground truth for feature relevance.",
    "Therefore, it is inferred that saliency maps are useful if they enable performance that is on par with performance relying on human attention maps.",
    "Indeed, participants were able to classify image segments generated by attribution methods as accurately as humangenerated segments (Schuessler & Weiß, 2019).",
    "However, these effects strongly depend on the attribution method and image type (Müller, Thoß, et al., 2024).",
    "Confidence scores."
  ]
